  "texts": [
    "For each time step T, the LSTM would take the current input x t and the previous hidden state h t - 1 and would produce a new hidden state h t and output y t.",
    "This process allows the LSTM to maintain information over time and is particularly useful for tasks such as speech and neural signal processing, where temporal dependencies are critical.",
    "Here we use three layers of LSTM and one linear layer to generate features to map to speech parameters.",
    "Unlike 3D ResNet and 3D Swin, we keep the temporal dimension unchanged across all layers.",
    "Training of the speech encoder and speech synthesizer."
  ],
